replies.bodyText:
That's a good question in fact, will it only be added dynamically when storing a content in cold storage? Or can we have some "cold storable content" documents, possibly stored in cold storage but not nevessarily?
@efge WDYT
Also, if at some point we decide that some content can be put back from cold to regular storage, then I guess that the facet won't be a synonym of "coldly stored"...

@ataillefer @RSalem07
My idea was to have it added dynamically only when a user/process decides to move to cold storage. But you're right that we could very well have doctypes that have this facet permanently. So the presence of the facet alone shouldn't be an indicator that something is in cold storage.
It's only when coldstorage:coldContent is not null then there's something in cold storage.

